<stack-static>
    <statement><p><p>
Solve the quadratic equation:
<me>
{x^2-x} = {7 x}
</me>
</p>

<p>
Write the solutions for <m>x</m>.
</p>

<p>
<m>x =</m> <fillin characters="15" name="ans1"/>   <m>\;or\;</m> <m>x =</m> <fillin characters="15" name="ans2"/> 
</p>
<p>  <m>\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;  </m> </p></p></statement>
    <solution><p><h3>Worked Solution</h3>

<p>
The equation given is:
</p>

<p>
<me>
{x^2-x} = {7 x}
</me>
</p>

<p>
Step 1: Subtract <m>{7 x}</m> from both sides so that the equation equals zero.
</p>

<p>
<me>
{x^2-x} - {7 x} = 0
</me>
</p>

<p>
This simplifies to:
</p>

<p>
<me>
{x^2-8 x} = 0
</me>
</p>

<p>
Step 2: Factorise the quadratic expression.
</p>

<p>
<me>
{x^2-8 x}
</me>
</p>

<p>
<me>
= (x - {0})(x - {8})
</me>
</p>

<p>
Step 3: Apply the zero product rule.
</p>

<p>
If the product of two expressions is zero, then at least one of the expressions must be zero.
</p>

<p>
<me>
x - {0} = 0 \quad \text{or} \quad x - {8} = 0
</me>
</p>

<p>
Step 4: Solve each equation.
</p>

<p>
<me>
x = {0}
</me>
</p>

<p>
or
</p>

<p>
<me>
x = {8}
</me>
</p>

<p>
Therefore, the solutions of the quadratic equation are:
</p>

<p>
<me>
x = {0},\;\;or\;\; x = {8}
</me>
</p></p></solution>
    <answer><p><m>0</m></p></answer>
    <answer><p><m>8</m></p></answer>
</stack-static>